# Shared Package Conventions

## Package Scopes

| Package | NPM Name | Purpose |
|---------|----------|---------|
| `packages/types` | `@centrai/types` | Domain types, Zod schemas, DTOs, event payloads |
| `packages/ui` | `@centrai/ui` | React component library (shadcn/ui based) |
| `packages/sdk` | `@centrai/sdk` | TypeScript API client for CentrAI |
| `packages/config` | `@centrai/config` | Shared ESLint, tsconfig, Prettier presets |

## Rules

- Packages must be **app-agnostic**. No imports from `apps/web` or `apps/api`.
- Every package has a barrel `src/index.ts` exporting its public API.
- Keep dependencies minimal — packages should not pull in heavy framework deps.

## @centrai/types

- Define Zod schemas first, derive TypeScript types with `z.infer<>`.
- Separate files: `api.ts` (DTOs), `models.ts` (domain entities), `events.ts` (WS/queue payloads).
- Types used by both frontend and backend go here. App-specific types stay in the app.

```typescript
// ✅ Schema-first approach
export const createAgentSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  systemPrompt: z.string().min(1),
  modelId: z.string().uuid(),
});
export type CreateAgentDto = z.infer<typeof createAgentSchema>;
```

## @centrai/ui

- Built on shadcn/ui. Export primitives from `primitives/` and composed components from `compositions/`.
- All components accept `className` prop for Tailwind overrides via `cn()`.
- Include dark mode support via CSS variables in `theme/`.
- No data fetching or business logic in UI components — props in, JSX out.

## @centrai/sdk

- Auto-generated from OpenAPI spec when possible.
- Typed methods per resource: `sdk.agents.list()`, `sdk.conversations.create()`.
- Support both `fetch` and streaming (WebSocket/SSE) transports.
